.
The Captain finding that it was in vain
to
to attempt by direct means to overcome the
force of prejudice, changed his language,
and affected to
suppose
that the valet might
be the devil, and
proposed
to examine the
extremity of both limbs, to
see
whether he
had a cloven foot. The valet,
summitting
to
