sand
.
Hard by the fall of this water, and on the
strand
of the river, the attention of the
Captain was attached by certain rude
sculptures
,
observable
on a flat rock; and
also
by others on a perpendicular one,
that
composed
a part of the bank. There
was the figure of the tarapin, the bear, the
turkey, &c. It was a
subject
of reflection
with the Captain, whether
these
impressions
had been made by the animals
themselves
,
while the rock had been in a
plastic
state
,
and before it had hardened from clay into
